### 🧰 Project & Architecture  
- [ ] Follows project architecture and layer boundaries  
- [ ] No unintended circular dependencies introduced  
- [ ] Solution and project files updated (e.g., `.sln`, `.csproj`)  
- [ ] No breaking changes to public APIs or contracts  

### 📚 Documentation  
- [ ] Public classes and methods are properly documented  
- [ ] README or related docs updated if necessary  
- [ ] Code comments added where logic may be complex or non-obvious  

### 📦 Dependencies & Config  
- [ ] NuGet or external dependencies updated only if needed  
- [ ] Build and runtime configurations are not broken  
- [ ] Environment-specific logic is feature-flagged or isolated  

### 🛡️ Security & Best Practices  
- [ ] No secrets, API keys, or credentials are exposed  
- [ ] Follows secure coding practices (e.g., input validation, error handling)  
- [ ] Logging is appropriate (no sensitive data)  

### 🔄 Process & Collaboration  
